at million-star spectral\nsurveys and photometric surveys targeting metal-poor stars already include\nhundreds of stars formed before $z=5$. We predict most of these targets to have\nhigher metallicity ($-3 < \\rm [Fe/H] < -2$) than the most extreme metal-poor\nstars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 Apr 2018 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Jul 2018 15:25:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-01"}
