 derived for the high-mass star-forming regions in Orion and the\nGalactic Centre. The low ratios indicate a grain surface temperature during\nformation ~30 K, for which the efficiency of the formation of deuterated\nspecies is significantly reduced.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Apr 2018 14:43:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-25"}
